## 1. Project Overview

**ArshadForge** is a **production-grade, agentic intelligence backend** designed to analyze a single PDF document тАФ the *"State of the Cyber Security Sector in Ireland 2022 Report"*. It converts this report into a **queryable, auditable intelligence platform** using a deterministic, tool-augmented pipeline rather than a naive RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) system.

### Core Philosophy (3 Principles)

| Principle | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Determinism** | No LLM reasoning for data retrieval, math, or planning. All numeric answers come from SQL or Python `eval()`. |
| **Auditability** | Every query produces a full JSON trace with tool inputs, outputs, timing, and success/failure status. |
| **Minimal LLM Dependence** | The LLM (`llama3:8b` via Ollama) is used **only** for composing final natural language answers from pre-computed data, and even then only for the "general" intent. |

### Technology Stack

| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| Web Framework | FastAPI + Uvicorn |
| Vector Database | ChromaDB (persistent, local) |
| Relational Database | SQLite (WAL mode, row_factory) |
| Embedding Model | `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (384-dim) |
| LLM | Ollama with `llama3:8b` (local) |
| PDF Parser | `pdfplumber` |
| Tokenizer | `tiktoken` (cl100k_base encoding) |
| HTTP Client | `httpx` |
| Config | `python-dotenv` (.env file) |

