## 3. ETL Pipeline тАФ In Depth

### 3.1 [extract.py](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py) (169 lines)

**Purpose**: Reads the PDF with `pdfplumber` and produces a list of **element dicts**, each either a `"text"` block or a `"table"`.

#### Key Functions

| Function | Lines | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| [_clean_text](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py#L21-L25) | 21тАУ25 | Collapses whitespace, strips non-printable chars while preserving common Unicode (тВм, accented Latin chars) |
| [_is_ocr_garbage](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py#L28-L34) | 28тАУ34 | Heuristic: if >50% of tokens are single characters тЖТ skip that page's text |
| [_detect_heading](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py#L37-L51) | 37тАУ51 | Classifies lines as headings via two heuristics: numbered sections (e.g., `3.2 NUMBER OF FIRMS`) or ALL-CAPS lines >10 chars |
| [_clean_header](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py#L54-L61) | 54тАУ61 | Normalizes individual table column headers; reject headers >120 chars |
| [_clean_headers](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py#L64-L73) | 64тАУ73 | Cleans all headers; replaces empty ones with positional fallbacks (`Column_1`, `Column_2`, etc.) |
| [_parse_table](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py#L76-L104) | 76тАУ104 | Converts raw pdfplumber 2D arrays into structured `{columns, rows, page}` dicts. Skips tables with <2 rows. |
| [extract_pdf](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/etl/extract.py#L107-L168) | 107тАУ168 | **Main entry point.** Iterates pages, detects headings, emits text blocks (min 50 chars) and tables. Tracks `current_section` across pages. |

#### Design Decisions
- **No OCR support**: Scanned PDFs with no embedded text are not handled.
- **Minimum text threshold**: Pages with <50 chars of cleaned text are skipped (catches headers/footers).
- **Section tracking**: Headings persist across pages. If a section spans multiple pages, all text blocks under it inherit the same section label.

