#### [_compose_answer](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/agents/graph.py#L726-L848) тАФ Answer Generation

| Intent | Method | LLM Used? |
|---|---|---|
| `arithmetic` | Direct echo: `"Calculation (expr) = result"` | тЭМ |
| `verification` | Template: job count + page + citation status | тЭМ |
| `data_synthesis` | Template: South-West % vs national %, comparison | тЭМ |
| `forecasting` | Template: baseline, target, CAGR %, formula, source | тЭМ |
| `employment_stats` | Template: total, percentage, absolute employee count | тЭМ |
| `general` | **LLM** (Ollama llama3:8b, temp=0.1, max 512 tokens) | тЬЕ |

> [!NOTE]
> The LLM is called only for general/unclassified queries. For all structured intents, the answer is built from Python string templates using pre-computed tool results. This is a key reliability feature.

#### [_call_llm](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/agents/graph.py#L850-L877)
- Sends system + user prompt to Ollama's `/api/chat` endpoint
- Temperature: 0.1 (nearly deterministic)
- Max tokens: 512
- Timeout: 120 seconds
- Graceful error handling for connection failures

#### Confidence Scoring ([run() method, lines 186-211](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/agents/graph.py#L186-L211))

Score is computed additively:
- +0.3 if SQL query succeeded
- +0.2 if calculator succeeded
- +0.2 if citation was valid (+0.05 if tool ran but failed)
- +0.2 if sources exist
- +0.1 if no validation errors
- тИТ0.2 if vector retrieval failed
- тИТ0.1 for each other failed tool

Clamped to [0.0, 1.0].

#### Source Extraction & Pruning ([_extract_sources](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/agents/graph.py#L881-L948))
- Gathers vector hits from `vector_data` and `vector_context` keys
- **Strict SQL mode** (`STRICT_SQL_SOURCES=true`): drops all vector citations if SQL data exists
- Delegates pruning to [citation_pruner.py](file:///Users/arshadshaik/Desktop/ArshadForge/agents/citation_pruner.py)
- Always includes SQL-derived hardcoded sources (Page 27, Page 15, Page 34)

